The paper deals with the problem of identifying graphs with small color classes using the Weisfeiler-Leman algorithm, which is a common topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves the study of graph structures and configurations, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of algorithms to solve the problem suggests a connection to theoretical computer science (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
